# gen160 E1: analytical composition over FRESH vocab (bryn/hound/companion).
# One conversation forces seven independently-evolved subsystems to cooperate:
# rule intake, fact intake, deductive query, contrastive abduction (why-not),
# optimal abduction (cheapest repair), self-correction (re-derive), proof, and
# robustness (load-bearing analysis). None of these names appears in tests/cases.
#subsystems: rule-intake, fact-intake, deduction, contrastive-abduction, optimal-abduction, self-correction, proof, robustness
#expect: pass
#class: composes-unchanged
> every loyal hound is a companion
< learned rule companion
> bryn is a hound
< learned houndbryn
> is bryn a companion?
< no
> why isn't bryn a companion?
< missing bryn is a loyal
> what is the easiest way to make bryn a companion?
< easiest way
> bryn is loyal
< now bryn is a companion after all
> why is bryn a companion?
< companionbryn because
> how robust is that conclusion?
< rests on 2 loadbearing facts